        <h1>Cook Book</h1>
        <p><em>My First Recipe is</em><p>
        <blockquote>Blueberry Muffins</blockquote>
        <img src = "https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/03/12/10/29/blueberry-2136749_960_720.jpg" width="480" height="320" >
        <h3>List of Ingredients</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>&frac12; cup butter or &frac12; cup margarine, at room temp</li>
            <li>1 cup granulated sugar</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon vanilla</li>
            <li>2 teaspoons of baking powder</li>
            <li>&frac14; teaspoon salt</li>
            <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
            <li>1 cup milk</li>
            <li>2 &frac12; cups fresh blueberries or 2 &frac12; cups frozen blueberries</li>
            
        </ol>
        <h3>Directions!</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Heat oven to 375Â°.</li>
            <li>Grease 18 regular-size muffin cups (or 12 large size muffins).</li>
            <li>In bowl, mix butter until creamy. Add sugar and beat until pale and fluffy.</li>
            <li>Add eggs one at a time, beating after each</li>
            <li>Beat in vanilla, baking powder and salt.</li>
            <li>With spoon, fold in half of flour then half of milk into batter; repeat.</li>
            <li>Fold in blueberries.</li>
            <li>Spoon into muffin cups and sprinkle topping onto each muffin.</li>
            <li>Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown and springy to touch.</li>
        </ol>
        <em><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZZXM-Jmbqts"> Here's the link to a youtube tutorial I found, might help! </a> </em>
